# Accessibility

Target practical WCAG 2.2 AA on core flows (browse → PDP → cart → checkout → account).

## Required

- Visible focus rings using theme tokens
- Keyboard access for dialogs, menus, builder steps, cart drawers
- Icon-only controls need `aria-label`
- Tap targets ≥ 48px (primary CTAs often 56px)
- Don’t convey status by color alone
- Form errors tied to fields + announced appropriately
- Meaningful `alt` on product images; decorative marked
- Honor `prefers-reduced-motion` (see GSAP rule)
- Modals: focus trap + Escape + restore focus

Tag chips (must/rec/nice) use dark text on pastel fills for contrast.
